# Patch: blob-inline-frontmatter

Inlines `parseFrontmatter` from upstream `src/frontmatter.ts` into
`vendor/vercel-skills/blob.ts`.

## Rationale

ADR-002 §Vendoring enumerates exactly five vendored modules:
`telemetry.ts`, `types.ts`, `source-parser.ts`, `blob.ts`, `find.ts`.
Adding `frontmatter.ts` as a sixth would require an ADR amendment.

`blob.ts` upstream does:

```ts
import { parseFrontmatter } from './frontmatter.ts';
```

To stay within the ADR boundary, the body of upstream `frontmatter.ts`
(7 LOC of executable code) is inlined as a private function near the
top of the vendored `blob.ts`. The runtime dependency on the `yaml`
package is moved into `server/package.json`.

## Changed lines in blob.ts

```diff
- import { parseFrontmatter } from './frontmatter.ts';
+ import { parse as parseYaml } from 'yaml';
+
+ // ─── Inlined frontmatter parser (upstream src/frontmatter.ts) ───
+
+ function parseFrontmatter(raw: string): {
+   data: Record<string, unknown>;
+   content: string;
+ } {
+   const match = raw.match(/^---\r?\n([\s\S]*?)\r?\n---\r?\n?([\s\S]*)$/);
+   if (!match) return { data: {}, content: raw };
+   const data = (parseYaml(match[1]!) as Record<string, unknown>) ?? {};
+   return { data, content: match[2] ?? '' };
+ }
```

(Plus the import path rewrite `'./types.ts'` → `'./types.js'` for ESM
NodeNext resolution — see `import-extensions.patch`.)

## Drift-check guidance

When re-fetching `src/blob.ts` from upstream, the drift-check tool
should:
1. Replace upstream `import { parseFrontmatter } from './frontmatter.ts';`
   with the inlined block (or strip both sides before diffing).
2. Apply the `import-extensions.patch` rewrite.
3. Then compare the body of `tryBlobInstall`, `findSkillMdPaths`,
   `fetchRepoTree`, and the helpers verbatim.
